OL,3,CLoan shark victim who 'lived in fear'
OL,4,Cwarns others of illegal lenders
OL,6,FShe said she lived in "fear" and would
OL,7,Fforego paying other bills such as
OL,8,F"council tax, rent, gas, electricity"
OL,9,Fjust so she would have more to pay the
OL,10,Floan shark and hopefully keep him away
OL,11,Ffrom her house and children.
OL,13,FBetween the threats and being told by
OL,14,Fthe loan shark that should anything
OL,15,Fhappen to her, any debt would be
OL,16,Fpassed to her children, she began to
OL,17,Fstruggle with her mental health and
OL,18,Fcould no longer work.
OL,20,F"I stopped leaving the house, I
OL,21,Fwouldn't go out anywhere," she added.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/12
